([[Wiktionary:Finnish_index_v|index V]])

===Etymology===
From the name of an area in Estonia, the modern Estonian form of which is ''Viru'' &ndash; reflected in the present-day names of ''Lääne-Virumaa'' and ''Ida-Virumaa'' (West and East Viru Counties).

===Noun===
'''viro'''

# the [[Estonian]] language.

